THE world is very evil;

The times are waxing late; Be sober and keep vigil, The Judge is at the gate;

The Judge that comes in memy, The J udge that comes with might, To terminate the evil,

To diadem the right.

Arise, arise, good Christian, Let right to wrong succeed3 Let penitential sorrow

To heavenly gladness lead,

To the light that hath no evening, That knows nor moon nor sun, The light so new and golden, The light that is but one.

O home of fadeless splendor, Of flowers that bear no thorn,

Where they shall dwell as children

Who here as exiles mourn;
